---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — QuiKey AI Hub (macOS)"
  description="How QuiKey AI Hub handles your data: AI providers you choose, local storage, optional analytics, and no QuiKey server storage of your content."
  productName="QuiKey AI Hub"
  navLinks={[
    { href: '/aihub/', label: 'AI Hub' },
    { href: '/aihub/#download', label: 'Download' },
    { href: '/blog', label: 'Blog' },
  ]}
  footerLinks={[
    { href: '/aihub/', label: 'AI Hub' },
    { href: '/aihub/privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
    { href: '/aihub/app-privacy-labels', label: 'App Privacy (labels)' },
    { href: '/terms', label: 'Terms' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="privacy-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="privacy-content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy — QuiKey AI Hub</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>

        <p>
          <strong>QuiKey AI Hub</strong> (the “App”) is the AI-focused flavor of the QuiKey family for macOS. This policy
          describes how the App handles data. It is written to align with the Mac App Store
          <a href="/aihub/app-privacy-labels">privacy nutrition label</a> and App Store Connect disclosures.
        </p>

        <section class="data-handling">
          <h2>1. What the App does</h2>
          <p>
            The App helps you run AI actions on files and selected text (Finder and Services), and use AI chats and squads
            inside the app. Processing uses <strong>third-party AI and tooling services that you configure</strong>
            (for example OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini, OpenRouter, or browser-based flows where applicable).
          </p>
          <p>
            This flavor <strong>does not include Gmail or Google Drive upload features</strong>. If you use another QuiKey
            flavor that does, that flavor’s privacy description applies there.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Data you actively send to third parties</h2>
          <p>
            When you invoke a feature, the App may send <strong>only what is needed for that request</strong> to the
            provider you chose—for example file contents or selected text, plus prompts and model parameters you control.
            Those transfers are governed by <strong>that provider’s terms and privacy policy</strong>, not by a separate
            QuiKey-hosted “AI backend.”
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google (Gemini)</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Local storage on your Mac</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Credentials and settings:</strong> API keys, provider preferences, and related configuration are stored
              locally on your device (for example in the app’s container / Application Support area). They are not sent to
              QuiKey servers for storage.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>History and chats:</strong> Conversation history and similar data are kept locally as part of the app’s
              functionality unless you delete them in the App.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Logs:</strong> Diagnostic logs may be stored locally and can be removed by you where the App provides
              controls.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Optional analytics (opt-in)</h2>
          <p>
            If you enable usage metrics in Settings, the App may send <strong>pseudonymous analytics</strong> (for example a
            device identifier, feature usage, and success or failure signals) to help improve stability and product
            quality. <strong>Analytics does not include your file contents, selected text contents, or chat message
            bodies.</strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            To opt out: <strong>Settings → General → disable “Send usage metrics.”</strong> When disabled, the analytics SDK
            is not initialized for that launch configuration.
          </p>
          <p>
            Analytics is processed using a third-party analytics provider configured in the App (see
            <a href="/aihub/app-privacy-labels">App Privacy labels</a> for the App Store–style breakdown).
          </p>

          <h2>5. Payments and licensing</h2>
          <p>
            Purchases or license management may be handled through third-party commerce providers (for example Lemon
            Squeezy). Payment and account data for those flows are subject to the provider’s policies.
          </p>

          <h2>6. No QuiKey server copy of your AI content</h2>
          <p>
            QuiKey does not operate a service that stores your files, prompts, or AI responses on our servers as part of the
            App’s core operation. Network connections are made from your Mac to the providers you configure, and to
            optional services such as analytics or licensing, as described above.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions: <a href="mailto:support@quikey.app">support@quikey.app</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Related: <a href="/aihub/app-privacy-labels">App Privacy (nutrition labels)</a> ·
            <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> · <a href="/privacy">General QuiKey privacy policy</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-page {
    padding: 120px 0 60px;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .privacy-content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .privacy-content h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .privacy-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .privacy-content p {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .privacy-content ul {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .privacy-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .privacy-content a {
    color: #3b82f6;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .privacy-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .privacy-content strong {
    color: #1f2937;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .privacy-page {
      padding: 100px 0 40px;
    }

    .privacy-content h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
